This paper involves the analysis of social media data, specifically Instagram, using computational methods. The focus is on image recognition and content analysis, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The use of hashtags and social network information also suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and social networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (cs.CL) in the analysis of hashtags. Overall, cs.SI and cs.MM are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.CV, cs.CL, and cs.IR.
